OL,3,CNew law for food allergen labels
OL,4,Cdelayed in Jersey
OL,6,FThe Environment Minster also stated
OL,7,Fthat The Food Safety (Labelling)
OL,8,F(Jersey) Order 2005 says that these
OL,9,Fimported products are compliant with
OL,10,Fthe island's legislation, provided
OL,11,Fthey are in the language understood by
OL,12,Fthe customer.
OL,14,FCurrent legislation also rules against
OL,15,Fmisrepresenting food. That means
OL,16,Fclaiming that a product is safe for an
OL,17,Fallergic customer when it is not.
